data.enText: the activity of fighting a war, especially using particular weapons or methods

data.chText: （群体、公司等之间的）斗争，竞争，冲突
data.enText: the activity of competing in an aggressive way with another group, company, etc.

data.chText: 争论很快恶化，演变成了公开的论战。
data.enText: The debate soon degenerated into open warfare.

means: (群体、公司等之间的)斗争，竞争，冲突

tr: the waging of armed conflict against an enemy
example: thousands of people were killed in the war

tr: an active struggle between competing entities

value.def: Warfare is the activity of fighting a war.
Warfare is sometimes used to refer to any violent struggle or conflict.

example.ex: Much of the violence is related to drugs and gang warfare...
example.tran: 大多数暴力事件都与吸毒和群殴有关。

example.ex: At times party rivalries have broken out into open warfare.
example.tran: 政党间的矛盾有时爆发为公开的冲突。
